Preheat your grill to high. Put @Low Fat Natural Yoghurt{1%tbsp per person} into a #medium bowl{} along with a quarter of the @Korma Curry Paste{50%g}, @Diced Chicken Thigh{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

== Prepare Vegetables ==

Trim the root from the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, thinly slice. Trim the @Spring Onion{2} then slice thinly. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @Black Beans{1%can} in a #sieve{}.

== Cook Chicken ==

Pop the chicken onto a foil lined #baking tray{}, spread out in a single layer. Pop under the grill until the chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}. Turn halfway.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the grill and set aside.

== Indian Style Refried Beans ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the @garlic{}, half of the @spring onions{} and remaining @Korma Curry Paste{}. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @black beans{} and @Chicken Stock Powder{1%tsp} and @Water for the Beans{50%ml}. Bring to the boil.

Reduce the heat slightly and gently, mash the beans with a #fork{} or #potato masher{} as they cook. Simmer until the mixture has thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring frequently.

> TIP: Add a splash more water if dry.

== Warm Tortillas ==

Arrange the @Plain Taco Tortillas{6} in one layer on another #baking tray{}. Place the tray under the chicken and warm for ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Serve ==

Serve the tacos with a spoonful of the re-fried beans, topped with sliced lettuce and grilled chicken. Finish with a drizzle of yogurt and the remaining spring onions. Enjoy!